  • Reference
Implements the Double Super Learner framework for right-censored survival data. Automatically constructs optimal convex combinations of parametric, semi-parametric, and machine learning base learners to minimize cross-validated risk using Inverse Probability of Censoring Weights (IPCW). Features include high-dimensional variable screening (Elastic Net, Marginal, Variance), automated hyperparameter tuning grids, rigorous performance evaluation (Brier Score, Uno's C-index, time-dependent AUC), and clinical calibration metrics. Provides robust global and local interpretability for complex survival ensembles via Kernel SHAP and time-dependent explanations.
